{
  "video_id": "PYHd7rpOTe8",
  "title": "Robert Gordon: The death of innovation, the end of growth",
  "es": 1,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 0.0,
      "end_time": 7000.0,
      "text": "Translator: Joseph Geni Reviewer: Morton Bast"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 12713.0,
      "end_time": 15421.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s how we traveled in the year 1900."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 15422.0,
      "end_time": 17791.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s an open buggy. It doesn&#39;t have heating."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 17791.0,
      "end_time": 19420.0,
      "text": "It doesn&#39;t have air conditioning."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 19420.0,
      "end_time": 21477.0,
      "text": "That horse is pulling it along"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 21477.0,
      "end_time": 23775.0,
      "text": "at one percent of the speed of sound,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 23775.0,
      "end_time": 25526.0,
      "text": "and the rutted dirt road"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 25527.0,
      "end_time": 29909.0,
      "text": "turns into a quagmire of mud anytime it rains."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 29909.0,
      "end_time": 32653.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s a Boeing 707."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 32654.000000000004,
      "end_time": 34955.0,
      "text": "Only 60 years later, it travels"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 34955.0,
      "end_time": 37172.0,
      "text": "at 80 percent of the speed of sound,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 37172.0,
      "end_time": 39805.0,
      "text": "and we don&#39;t travel any faster today"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 39805.0,
      "end_time": 42944.0,
      "text": "because commercial supersonic air travel"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 42944.0,
      "end_time": 44913.0,
      "text": "turned out to be a bust."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 44913.0,
      "end_time": 47464.0,
      "text": "So I started wondering and pondering,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 47465.0,
      "end_time": 50487.0,
      "text": "could it be that the best years of American economic growth"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 50487.0,
      "end_time": 52146.0,
      "text": "are behind us?"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 52146.0,
      "end_time": 56625.0,
      "text": "And that leads to the suggestion, maybe economic growth"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 56625.0,
      "end_time": 58852.0,
      "text": "is almost over."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 58852.0,
      "end_time": 62614.0,
      "text": "Some of the reasons for this are not really very controversial."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 62614.0,
      "end_time": 64988.0,
      "text": "There are four headwinds that are just hitting"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 64988.0,
      "end_time": 67373.0,
      "text": "the American economy in the face."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 67373.0,
      "end_time": 72310.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re demographics, education, debt and inequality."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 72310.0,
      "end_time": 75664.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re powerful enough to cut growth in half."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 75664.0,
      "end_time": 80322.0,
      "text": "So we need a lot of innovation to offset this decline."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 80322.0,
      "end_time": 83900.0,
      "text": "And here&#39;s my theme: Because of the headwinds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 83900.0,
      "end_time": 85771.0,
      "text": "if innovation continues to be as powerful as it has been"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 85771.0,
      "end_time": 89638.0,
      "text": "in the last 150 years, growth is cut in half."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 89638.0,
      "end_time": 92349.0,
      "text": "If innovation is less powerful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 92349.0,
      "end_time": 94803.0,
      "text": "invents less great, wonderful things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 94803.0,
      "end_time": 98813.0,
      "text": "then growth is going to be even lower than half of history."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 98813.0,
      "end_time": 101968.0,
      "text": "Now here&#39;s eight centuries of economic growth."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 101968.0,
      "end_time": 105632.0,
      "text": "The vertical axis is just percent per year of growth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 105632.0,
      "end_time": 108755.0,
      "text": "zero percent a year, one percent a year, two percent a year."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 108755.0,
      "end_time": 111655.0,
      "text": "The white line is for the U.K., and then the U.S."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 111655.0,
      "end_time": 114186.0,
      "text": "takes over as the leading nation in the year 1900,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 114186.0,
      "end_time": 115677.0,
      "text": "when the line switches to red."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 115677.0,
      "end_time": 117663.0,
      "text": "You&#39;ll notice that, for the first four centuries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 117663.0,
      "end_time": 121533.0,
      "text": "there&#39;s hardly any growth at all, just 0.2 percent."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 121533.0,
      "end_time": 123152.0,
      "text": "Then growth gets better and better."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 123152.0,
      "end_time": 126130.0,
      "text": "It maxes out in the 1930s, &#39;40s and &#39;50s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 126130.0,
      "end_time": 129887.0,
      "text": "and then it starts slowing down, and here&#39;s a cautionary note."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 129887.0,
      "end_time": 132383.0,
      "text": "That last downward notch in the red line"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 132383.0,
      "end_time": 134614.0,
      "text": "is not actual data."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 134614.0,
      "end_time": 137754.0,
      "text": "That is a forecast that I made six years ago"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 137754.0,
      "end_time": 140382.0,
      "text": "that growth would slow down to 1.3 percent."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 140383.0,
      "end_time": 142393.0,
      "text": "But you know what the actual facts are?"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 142393.0,
      "end_time": 144206.0,
      "text": "You know what the growth in per-person income has been"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 144206.0,
      "end_time": 147970.0,
      "text": "in the United States in the last six years?"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 147980.0,
      "end_time": 149438.0,
      "text": "Negative."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 149438.0,
      "end_time": 151708.0,
      "text": "This led to a fantasy."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 151709.0,
      "end_time": 156955.0,
      "text": "What if I try to fit a curved line to this historical record?"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 156955.0,
      "end_time": 160923.0,
      "text": "I can make the curved line end anywhere I wanted,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 160923.0,
      "end_time": 163717.0,
      "text": "but I decided I would end it at 0.2,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 163717.0,
      "end_time": 168542.0,
      "text": "just like the U.K. growth for the first four centuries."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 168542.0,
      "end_time": 171906.0,
      "text": "Now the history that we&#39;ve achieved is that we&#39;ve grown"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 171906.0,
      "end_time": 175967.0,
      "text": "at 2.0 percent per year over the whole period,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 175967.0,
      "end_time": 179155.0,
      "text": "1891 to 2007,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 179155.0,
      "end_time": 182779.0,
      "text": "and remember it&#39;s been a little bit negative since 2007."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 182779.0,
      "end_time": 185840.0,
      "text": "But if growth slows down,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 185840.0,
      "end_time": 189670.0,
      "text": "instead of doubling our standard of living every generation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 189670.0,
      "end_time": 193905.0,
      "text": "Americans in the future can&#39;t expect to be twice as well off as their parents,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 193905.0,
      "end_time": 196875.0,
      "text": "or even a quarter [more well off than] their parents."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 196875.0,
      "end_time": 201240.0,
      "text": "Now we&#39;re going to change and look at the level of per capita income."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 201240.0,
      "end_time": 204604.0,
      "text": "The vertical axis now is thousands of dollars in today&#39;s prices."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 204604.0,
      "end_time": 207180.0,
      "text": "You&#39;ll notice that in 1891, over on the left,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 207180.0,
      "end_time": 208910.0,
      "text": "we were at about 5,000 dollars."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 208910.0,
      "end_time": 211815.0,
      "text": "Today we&#39;re at about 44,000 dollars of total output"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 211815.0,
      "end_time": 214482.0,
      "text": "per member of the population."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 214482.0,
      "end_time": 216900.0,
      "text": "Now what if we could achieve that historic"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 216900.0,
      "end_time": 219883.0,
      "text": "two-percent growth for the next 70 years?"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 219883.0,
      "end_time": 221215.0,
      "text": "Well, it&#39;s a matter of arithmetic."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 221215.0,
      "end_time": 225355.0,
      "text": "Two-percent growth quadruples your standard of living in 70 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 225355.0,
      "end_time": 229550.0,
      "text": "That means we&#39;d go from 44,000 to 180,000."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 229560.0,
      "end_time": 231507.0,
      "text": "Well, we&#39;re not going to do that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 231507.0,
      "end_time": 233333.0,
      "text": "and the reason is the headwinds."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 233333.0,
      "end_time": 234974.0,
      "text": "The first headwind is demographics."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 234974.0,
      "end_time": 237311.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a truism that your standard of living"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 237312.0,
      "end_time": 240824.0,
      "text": "rises faster than productivity, rises faster than output per hour,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 240824.0,
      "end_time": 243434.0,
      "text": "if hours per person increased."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 243434.0,
      "end_time": 245936.0,
      "text": "And we got that gift back in the &#39;70s and &#39;80s"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 245936.0,
      "end_time": 248454.0,
      "text": "when women entered the labor force."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 248454.0,
      "end_time": 250691.0,
      "text": "But now it&#39;s turned around."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 250691.0,
      "end_time": 252891.0,
      "text": "Now hours per person are shrinking,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 252891.0,
      "end_time": 255765.0,
      "text": "first because of the retirement of the baby boomers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 255765.0,
      "end_time": 259918.0,
      "text": "and second because there&#39;s been a very significant"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 259918.0,
      "end_time": 263916.0,
      "text": "dropping out of the labor force of prime age adult males"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 263916.0,
      "end_time": 267854.0,
      "text": "who are in the bottom half of the educational distribution."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 267854.0,
      "end_time": 270150.0,
      "text": "The next headwind is education."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 270150.0,
      "end_time": 272659.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve got problems all over our educational system"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 272660.0,
      "end_time": 274181.0,
      "text": "despite Race to the Top."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 274181.0,
      "end_time": 278263.0,
      "text": "In college, we&#39;ve got cost inflation in higher education"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 278263.0,
      "end_time": 281174.0,
      "text": "that dwarfs cost inflation in medical care."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 281175.0,
      "end_time": 285431.0,
      "text": "We have in higher education a trillion dollars of student debt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 285431.0,
      "end_time": 288418.0,
      "text": "and our college completion rate"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 288418.0,
      "end_time": 295369.0,
      "text": "is 15 points, 15 percentage points below Canada."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 295369.0,
      "end_time": 297476.0,
      "text": "We have a lot of debt."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 297476.0,
      "end_time": 302458.0,
      "text": "Our economy grew from 2000 to 2007"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 302458.0,
      "end_time": 305690.0,
      "text": "on the back of consumers massively overborrowing."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 305690.0,
      "end_time": 308626.0,
      "text": "Consumers paying off that debt is one of the main reasons"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 308626.0,
      "end_time": 311361.0,
      "text": "why our economic recovery is so sluggish today."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 311362.0,
      "end_time": 312948.0,
      "text": "And everybody of course knows"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 312948.0,
      "end_time": 315770.0,
      "text": "that the federal government debt is growing"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 315770.0,
      "end_time": 318406.0,
      "text": "as a share of GDP at a very rapid rate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 318406.0,
      "end_time": 321568.0,
      "text": "and the only way that&#39;s going to stop is some combination"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 321568.0,
      "end_time": 326645.0,
      "text": "of faster growth in taxes or slower growth in entitlements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 326645.0,
      "end_time": 328729.0,
      "text": "also called transfer payments."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 328730.0,
      "end_time": 330899.0,
      "text": "And that gets us down from the 1.5,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 330899.0,
      "end_time": 334300.0,
      "text": "where we&#39;ve reached for education, down to 1.3."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 334300.0,
      "end_time": 336718.0,
      "text": "And then we have inequality."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 336718.0,
      "end_time": 339471.0,
      "text": "Over the 15 years before the financial crisis,"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 339471.0,
      "end_time": 342737.0,
      "text": "the growth rate of the bottom 99 percent"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 342737.0,
      "end_time": 345860.0,
      "text": "of the income distribution was half a point slower"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 345860.0,
      "end_time": 348636.0,
      "text": "than the averages we&#39;ve been talking about before."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 348636.0,
      "end_time": 350922.0,
      "text": "All the rest went to the top one percent."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 350922.0,
      "end_time": 353274.0,
      "text": "So that brings us down to 0.8."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 353274.0,
      "end_time": 356649.0,
      "text": "And that 0.8 is the big challenge."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 356649.0,
      "end_time": 358863.0,
      "text": "Are we going to grow at 0.8?"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 358863.0,
      "end_time": 361318.0,
      "text": "If so, that&#39;s going to require that our inventions"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 361318.0,
      "end_time": 363664.0,
      "text": "are as important as the ones that happened"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 363665.0,
      "end_time": 366583.0,
      "text": "over the last 150 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 366583.0,
      "end_time": 370622.0,
      "text": "So let&#39;s see what some of those inventions were."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 370622.0,
      "end_time": 374124.0,
      "text": "If you wanted to read in 1875 at night,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 374124.0,
      "end_time": 377446.0,
      "text": "you needed to have an oil or a gas lamp."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 377446.0,
      "end_time": 379603.0,
      "text": "They created pollution, they created odors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 379603.0,
      "end_time": 382800.0,
      "text": "they were hard to control, the light was dim,"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 382800.0,
      "end_time": 384156.0,
      "text": "and they were a fire hazard."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 384156.0,
      "end_time": 389251.0,
      "text": "By 1929, electric light was everywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 389251.0,
      "end_time": 393400.0,
      "text": "We had the vertical city, the invention of the elevator."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 393400.0,
      "end_time": 396385.0,
      "text": "Central Manhattan became possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 396385.0,
      "end_time": 399632.0,
      "text": "And then, in addition to that, at the same time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 399632.0,
      "end_time": 403128.0,
      "text": "hand tools were replaced by massive electric tools"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 403128.0,
      "end_time": 405836.0,
      "text": "and hand-powered electric tools,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 405836.0,
      "end_time": 408694.0,
      "text": "all achieved by electricity."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 408694.0,
      "end_time": 412907.0,
      "text": "Electricity was also very helpful in liberating women."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 412907.0,
      "end_time": 415594.0,
      "text": "Women, back in the late 19th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 415595.0,
      "end_time": 418251.0,
      "text": "spent two days a week doing the laundry."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 418251.0,
      "end_time": 419965.0,
      "text": "They did it on a scrub board."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 419966.0,
      "end_time": 422340.0,
      "text": "Then they had to hang the clothes out to dry."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 422340.0,
      "end_time": 423566.0,
      "text": "Then they had to bring them in."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 423566.0,
      "end_time": 426518.0,
      "text": "The whole thing took two days out of the seven-day week."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 426519.0,
      "end_time": 430106.0,
      "text": "And then we had the electric washing machine."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 430106.0,
      "end_time": 433180.0,
      "text": "And by 1950, they were everywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 433180.0,
      "end_time": 436208.0,
      "text": "But the women still had to shop every day,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 436208.0,
      "end_time": 438500.0,
      "text": "but no they didn&#39;t, because electricity"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 438500.0,
      "end_time": 441401.0,
      "text": "brought us the electric refrigerator."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 441401.0,
      "end_time": 444593.0,
      "text": "Back in the late 19th century, the only source of heat in most homes"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 444593.0,
      "end_time": 449122.0,
      "text": "was a big fireplace in the kitchen that was used for cooking and heating."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 449122.0,
      "end_time": 451438.0,
      "text": "The bedrooms were cold. They were unheated."
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 451438.0,
      "end_time": 454118.0,
      "text": "But by 1929, certainly by 1950,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 454118.0,
      "end_time": 458100.0,
      "text": "we had central heating everywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 458100.0,
      "end_time": 460602.0,
      "text": "What about the internal combustion engine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 460602.0,
      "end_time": 462941.0,
      "text": "which was invented in 1879?"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 462942.0,
      "end_time": 466760.0,
      "text": "In America, before the motor vehicle,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 466760.0,
      "end_time": 470732.0,
      "text": "transportation depended entirely on the urban horse,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 470732.0,
      "end_time": 473618.0,
      "text": "which dropped, without restraint,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 473618.0,
      "end_time": 477423.0,
      "text": "25 to 50 pounds of manure on the streets every day"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 477423.0,
      "end_time": 479347.0,
      "text": "together with a gallon of urine."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 479347.0,
      "end_time": 482560.0,
      "text": "That comes out at five to 10 tons daily"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 482560.0,
      "end_time": 484993.0,
      "text": "per square mile in cities."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 484993.0,
      "end_time": 490933.0,
      "text": "Those horses also ate up fully one quarter of American agricultural land."
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 490934.0,
      "end_time": 493332.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s the percentage of American agricultural land"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 493332.0,
      "end_time": 495525.0,
      "text": "it took to feed the horses."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 495525.0,
      "end_time": 499486.0,
      "text": "Of course, when the motor vehicle was invented,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 499487.0,
      "end_time": 502691.0,
      "text": "and it became almost ubiquitous by 1929,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 502691.0,
      "end_time": 505786.0,
      "text": "that agricultural land could be used for human consumption"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 505786.0,
      "end_time": 507320.0,
      "text": "or for export."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 507320.0,
      "end_time": 510960.0,
      "text": "And here&#39;s an interesting ratio: Starting from zero in 1900,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 510960.0,
      "end_time": 515876.0,
      "text": "only 30 years later, the ratio of motor vehicles to the number of households"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 515876.0,
      "end_time": 522459.0,
      "text": "in the United States reached 90 percent in just 30 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 522460.00000000006,
      "end_time": 525271.0,
      "text": "Back before the turn of the century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 525271.0,
      "end_time": 526671.0,
      "text": "women had another problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 526672.0,
      "end_time": 531267.0,
      "text": "All the water for cooking, cleaning and bathing"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 531267.0,
      "end_time": 535937.0,
      "text": "had to be carried in buckets and pails in from the outside."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 535937.0,
      "end_time": 538412.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s a historical fact that in 1885,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 538412.0,
      "end_time": 540726.0,
      "text": "the average North Carolina housewife"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 540726.0,
      "end_time": 546960.0,
      "text": "walked 148 miles a year carrying 35 tons of water."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 546960.0,
      "end_time": 550500.0,
      "text": "But by 1929, cities around the country"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 550500.0,
      "end_time": 553515.0,
      "text": "had put in underground water pipes."
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 553515.0,
      "end_time": 556941.0,
      "text": "They had put in underground sewer pipes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 556941.0,
      "end_time": 562123.0,
      "text": "and as a result, one of the great scourges of the late 19th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 562123.0,
      "end_time": 566369.0,
      "text": "waterborne diseases like cholera, began to disappear."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 566369.0,
      "end_time": 569971.0,
      "text": "And an amazing fact for techno-optimists"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 569971.0,
      "end_time": 572543.0,
      "text": "is that in the first half of the 20th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 572543.0,
      "end_time": 575255.0,
      "text": "the rate of improvement of life expectancy"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 575255.0,
      "end_time": 578560.0,
      "text": "was three times faster than it was"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 578560.0,
      "end_time": 580927.0,
      "text": "in the second half of the 19th century."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 580927.0,
      "end_time": 586130.0,
      "text": "So it&#39;s a truism that things can&#39;t be more than 100 percent of themselves."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 586130.0,
      "end_time": 588195.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;ll just give you a few examples."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 588195.0,
      "end_time": 591463.0,
      "text": "We went from one percent to 90 percent of the speed of sound."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 591463.0,
      "end_time": 595700.0,
      "text": "Electrification, central heat, ownership of motor cars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 595710.0,
      "end_time": 597434.0,
      "text": "they all went from zero to 100 percent."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 597434.0,
      "end_time": 601840.0,
      "text": "Urban environments make people more productive than on the farm."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 601840.0,
      "end_time": 603925.0,
      "text": "We went from 25 percent urban to 75 percent"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 603926.0,
      "end_time": 608540.0,
      "text": "by the early postwar years."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 608540.0,
      "end_time": 610297.0,
      "text": "What about the electronic revolution?"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 610297.0,
      "end_time": 612418.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s an early computer."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 612418.0,
      "end_time": 615728.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s amazing. The mainframe computer was invented in 1942."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 615728.0,
      "end_time": 620281.0,
      "text": "By 1960 we had telephone bills, bank statements"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 620281.0,
      "end_time": 622510.0,
      "text": "were being produced by computers."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 622520.0,
      "end_time": 624916.0,
      "text": "The earliest cell phones, the earliest personal computers"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 624916.0,
      "end_time": 627831.0,
      "text": "were invented in the 1970s."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 627831.0,
      "end_time": 631860.0,
      "text": "The 1980s brought us Bill Gates, DOS,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 631860.0,
      "end_time": 633871.0,
      "text": "ATM machines to replace bank tellers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 633871.0,
      "end_time": 637764.0,
      "text": "bar code scanning to cut down on labor in the retail sector."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 637764.0,
      "end_time": 639631.0,
      "text": "Fast forward through the &#39;90s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 639631.0,
      "end_time": 641199.0,
      "text": "we had the dotcom revolution"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 641199.0,
      "end_time": 644323.0,
      "text": "and a temporary rise in productivity growth."
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 644323.0,
      "end_time": 646775.0,
      "text": "But I&#39;m now going to give you an experiment."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 646775.0,
      "end_time": 649863.0,
      "text": "You have to choose either option A or option B."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 649863.0,
      "end_time": 652378.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 652378.0,
      "end_time": 655719.0,
      "text": "Option A is you get to keep everything invented up till 10 years ago."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 655719.0,
      "end_time": 658629.0,
      "text": "So you get Google, you get Amazon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 658629.0,
      "end_time": 661716.0,
      "text": "you get Wikipedia, and you get running water and indoor toilets."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 661716.0,
      "end_time": 663545.0,
      "text": "Or you get everything invented to yesterday,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 663545.0,
      "end_time": 665621.0,
      "text": "including Facebook and your iPhone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 665621.0,
      "end_time": 667980.0,
      "text": "but you have to give up, go out to the outhouse,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 667980.0,
      "end_time": 670844.0,
      "text": "and carry in the water."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 670844.0,
      "end_time": 674294.0,
      "text": "Hurricane Sandy caused a lot of people to lose the 20th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 674294.0,
      "end_time": 675817.0,
      "text": "maybe for a couple of days,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 675817.0,
      "end_time": 677943.0,
      "text": "in some cases for more than a week,"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 677943.0,
      "end_time": 681483.0,
      "text": "electricity, running water, heating, gasoline for their cars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 681483.0,
      "end_time": 684399.0,
      "text": "and a charge for their iPhones."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 684399.0,
      "end_time": 687910.0,
      "text": "The problem we face is that all these great inventions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 687910.0,
      "end_time": 690914.0,
      "text": "we have to match them in the future,"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 690914.0,
      "end_time": 693502.0,
      "text": "and my prediction that we&#39;re not going to match them"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 693502.0,
      "end_time": 696697.0,
      "text": "brings us down from the original two-percent growth"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 696697.0,
      "end_time": 701767.0,
      "text": "down to 0.2, the fanciful curve that I drew you at the beginning."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 701767.0,
      "end_time": 704774.0,
      "text": "So here we are back to the horse and buggy."
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 704774.0,
      "end_time": 707950.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d like to award an Oscar"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 707950.0,
      "end_time": 710748.0,
      "text": "to the inventors of the 20th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 710748.0,
      "end_time": 713489.0,
      "text": "the people from Alexander Graham Bell"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 713489.0,
      "end_time": 715192.0,
      "text": "to Thomas Edison to the Wright Brothers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 715192.0,
      "end_time": 716915.0,
      "text": "I&#39;d like to call them all up here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 716915.0,
      "end_time": 718785.0,
      "text": "and they&#39;re going to call back to you."
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 718785.0,
      "end_time": 722448.0,
      "text": "Your challenge is, can you match what we achieved?"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 722448.0,
      "end_time": 723982.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 723982.0,
      "end_time": 729120.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}